<h2 id=3D"isosceles-trapezoid-definition">Isosceles trapezoid definition</h=
2>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/trapez.png" a=
lt=3D""></p>
<p>An <strong>isosceles trapezoid</strong> (or <strong>trapez</strong>) is =
a trapezoid with legs that have equal length.</p>
<p>A <strong>trapezoid</strong> is a geometric shape with four sides, where=
 at least one pair of sides is parallel to each other. The two parallel sid=
es are called <strong>bases</strong>, and the other two sides are called <s=
trong>legs</strong>. If the legs are also parallel to each other, then we g=
et a parallelogram.</p>
<h2 id=3D"parts-of-an-isosceles-trapezoid">Parts of an isosceles trapezoid<=
/h2>
<p>There are eight parts of an isosceles trapezoid mentioned in this tool: =
long side (a), short side (b), legs (c), height (h), area (A), perimeter (P=
), diagonal (d) and circumradius (R).</p>
<h3 id=3D"long-and-short-sides-a-b">Long and short sides (a, b)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/long-and-shor=
t-sides.png" alt=3D""></p>
<p>The <strong>long</strong> and <strong>short</strong> sides are the two s=
ides that are parallel to each other. These two sides are known as the <str=
ong>bases</strong> of the isosceles trapezoid.</p>
<p>In our case, the <strong>long side (a)</strong> is the bottom base and t=
he <strong>short side (b)</strong> is the top base of the trapezoid.</p>
<p>To be able to calculate all values of an isosceles trapezoid, you must k=
now the value of at least one of the base sides. You can calculate the seco=
nd base with one of the following formulas:</p>
<p>To calculate all the values of an isosceles trapezoid, you need to know =
the value of at least one of the base sides and two other values. Then you =
can calculate the second base with one of the following formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>If you know the area and height:</p>
<p><code>a =3D 2 * A / h - b</code></p>
<p><code>b =3D 2 * A / h - a</code></p></li>
<li><p>If you know the height and diagonal:</p>
<p><code>a =3D 2 * =E2=88=9A(d=C2=B2 - h=C2=B2) - b</code></p>
<p><code>b =3D 2 * =E2=88=9A(d=C2=B2 - h=C2=B2) - a</code></p></li>
<li><p>If you know the diagonal and leg length:</p>
<p><code>a =3D (d=C2=B2 - c=C2=B2) / b</code></p>
<p><code>b =3D (d=C2=B2 - c=C2=B2) / a</code></p></li>
<li><p>If you know the leg length and perimeter:</p>
<p><code>a =3D P - b - 2 * c</code></p>
<p><code>b =3D P - a - 2 * c</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"legs-c">Legs (c)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/legs.png" alt=
=3D""></p>
<p>The <strong>legs</strong> of an isosceles trapezoid are the two sides th=
at are equal in length and connect the parallel sides (bases). They also fo=
rm two equal angles at the end of each parallel side.</p>
<p>To calculate the leg length, you need to know the length of the long bas=
e, the short base and one other value. Then you can use one of the followin=
g formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>If you know the height:</p>
<p><code>c =3D =E2=88=9A(4 * h=C2=B2 + (a - b)=C2=B2) / 2</code></p></li>
<li><p>If you know the diagonal:</p>
<p><code>c =3D =E2=88=9A(d=C2=B2 - a * b)</code></p></li>
<li><p>If you know the perimeter:</p>
<p><code>c =3D (P - a - b) / 2</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"height-h">Height (h)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/height.png" a=
lt=3D""></p>
<p>The <strong>height</strong> of an isosceles trapezoid is the perpendicul=
ar distance between the two parallel sides.</p>
<p>It can be calculated with the following formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>If you know all sides of the isosceles trapezoid:</p>
<p><code>h =3D =E2=88=9A(4 * c=C2=B2 - (a - b)=C2=B2) / 2</code></p></li>
<li><p>If you know the two bases and the circumference:</p>
<p><code>h =3D =E2=88=9A(R=C2=B2 - a=C2=B2 / 4) + =E2=88=9A(R=C2=B2 - b=C2=
=B2 / 4)</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"area-a">Area (A)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/area.png" alt=
=3D""></p>
<p>The <strong>area</strong> of an isosceles trapezoid is the region enclos=
ed inside the trapezoid.</p>
<p>It can be calculated by the formula:</p>
<p><code>A =3D (a + b) / 2 * h</code></p>
<h3 id=3D"perimeter-p">Perimeter (P)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/perimeter.png=
" alt=3D""></p>
<p>The <strong>perimeter</strong> of an isosceles trapezoid is the sum of t=
he lengths of all its sides.</p>
<p>The formula for calculating the perimeter of an isosceles trapezoid is:<=
/p>
<p><code>P =3D a + b + 2 * c</code></p>
<h3 id=3D"diagonal-d">Diagonal (d)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/diagonal.png"=
 alt=3D""></p>
<p>A <strong>diagonal</strong> of an isosceles trapezoid is a line segment =
that connects two non-adjacent vertices. In every isosceles trapezoid there=
 are two diagonals of equal length.</p>
<p>The formula for calculating the diagonal of an isosceles trapezoid is:</=
p>
<p><code>d =3D =E2=88=9A(a * b + c=C2=B2)</code></p>
<h3 id=3D"circumradius-r">Circumradius (R)</h3>
<p><img src=3D"https://calckit.io/tool_assets/geometry/trapez/circumradius.=
png" alt=3D""></p>
<p>The <strong>circumradius</strong> of an isosceles trapezoid is the radiu=
s of a circle that circumscribes the trapezoid, meaning that it passes thro=
ugh all vertices <em>(corners)</em> of the isosceles trapezoid.</p>
<p>The formulas for calculating the circumradius that CalcKit uses are the =
following:</p>
<pre><code>R =3D (c*d*b) / 4 / =E2=88=9A((c+d+b) / 2 * ((c+d+b) / 2 - c) * =
((c+d+b) / 2 - d)*((c+d+b) / 2 - b))
R =3D (c*d*a) / 4 / =E2=88=9A((c+d+a) / 2 * ((c+d+a) / 2 - c) * ((c+d+a) / =
2 - d)*((c+d+a) / 2 - a))
</code></pre></div>
